Perfection! I was looking for an easy but impressive dessert for a dinner party and stumbled across this tasty holiday cake. It is a nice change from the usual pumpkin or pecan pie. Also great for dinner party b/c it could be prepared in advance (actually much tastier that way) and iced just before serving. I followed the advice of others and increased the cinnamon and allspice amounts in the cake and also added some to the icing. Gave it a nice spicy kick. Cake was such a hit at the dinner party I made it again for a Thanksgiving potluck at my office and it got rave reviews. Had several people ask me for the recipe. It is THAT good folks. Would also try this in mini muffin tins, so that you get more icing per bite. Great as breakfast the next day too!

