A delicious cake for the season! I'd give it 3-1/2 forks if I could. Based on previous reviews which said the cake could use some spicing up I used the following: 1-1/4 teaspoons each of cinnamon and ginger; 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg; 1/4 teaspoon allspice; 1/4 teaspoon cloves. Also, if you don't want the icing to seep into the warm cake, just wait as I did for the cake to cool then drizzle on the icing! I also used a little vanilla in the icing as helpfully recommended by others.

