This was quite a good, moist cake. As per other suggestions, do double the cinnamon and the vanilla. I also added 1 tsp. of vanilla and a good shake of cinnamon to the frosting, then mixed it as the previous reviewer suggested. It should still be very thick, then just press on it a bit with a spatula and it will eventually ooze down the sides. A big hit with kids and adults!

Rating: 4
I have made this cake twice within a week. It is very straightforward, tasty and appealing. To achieve the result shown in the picture, add buttermilk (unmeasured)directly and gradually to the sugar, stirring until a very thick, barely pourable consistency is achieved. Drizzle carefully over the cake, so as little as possible drips onto the plate and most of the icing remains on the cake. It will then appear thick and white as shown. Delicious!

