Rating: 3
Very moist, excellent cake, would be perfect with tea or coffee. I substituted 1/4 tsp of ground ginger for some of the allspice. I agree that the spiciness is subtle, but I think increasing the spices too much more would completely overwhelm the pumpkin flavor which itself is subtle. For more spiciness, there are other spice cake recipes. By the way, by covering the cake in an airtight container and letting it sit a day or two, as recommended (and I agree), the icing pretty much melts into the surface of the cake,it doesn't 'harden' as the recipe indicates. I suppose one could make the cake ahead and ice it closer to serving. If anyone is thinking that the icing will be sour due to the buttermilk, it isn't, the sugar takes care of that.

Rating: 3
I would definitely add some additional spice to this recipe. It definitely improves with each day but it needs a bit more zing.. Very moist and delicious..